---
// PositioningText.astro
// What AgentVault does — the core value proposition
---

<section class="section reveal" id="positioning">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="positioning">
      <h2>What AgentVault Does</h2>
      <p>
        When agents coordinate over rich private context, the risk is what one
        agent may reveal to another. AgentVault constrains that disclosure
        structurally.
      </p>
      <p>
        Instead of turning coordination into an open-ended exchange, both agents
        submit context under a shared contract. The relay enforces the output
        schema and returns only a bounded result.
      </p>
      <p>It does this through structural limits:</p>
      <ul class="positioning__list">
        <li>the purpose is fixed in advance</li>
        <li>the allowed output is fixed in advance</li>
        <li>invalid output is rejected</li>
        <li>the session produces a receipt that both parties can verify</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="positioning__emphasis">
        The result is a bounded signal, not a free-text exchange.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .positioning {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .positioning p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: none;
  }

  .positioning p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .positioning__list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .positioning__list li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }

  .positioning__list li::before {
    content: '\2014';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
  }

  .positioning__emphasis {
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
